        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(googlechat): truncate approval card text on UTF-16 boundary",
        "body": "## Problem\n`truncateText` shortens Google Chat approval card text with a raw UTF-16 `.slice()`. An emoji near the character limit is cut into a lone surrogate that then pollutes the `cardsV2` API payload.\n\n## Fix\nUse the shared `truncateUtf16Safe` helper so truncation stops on a whole code-point boundary.\n\n## Proof\nAdded a regression in `extensions/googlechat/src/approval-handler.runtime.test.ts` asserting the card text stays well-formed — fails before, passes after. Pure unit test.\n",
